    <fr:title text="Inhabitation and existence">Inhabitation and existence</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <fr:p>A type <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is called <fr:em><fr:strong>inhabited</fr:strong></fr:em> when we have an element of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {toProp}\,A]]></fr:tex>. When we say <fr:em><fr:strong>there exists</fr:strong></fr:em>, we refer to inhabitation.</fr:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
