                <fr:p>A function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex> is called <fr:em><fr:strong>surjective</fr:strong></fr:em> when for any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b\colon  B]]></fr:tex>, the <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001Q.xml" title="Fiber" addr="//erct/erct-001Q" type="local">fiber</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-002A.xml" title="Inhabitation and existence" addr="//erct/erct-002A" type="local">inhabited</fr:link>.</fr:p>
